Business Brief -- Abitibi-Price Inc.:
   Loss Widened in Quarter;
   `Difficult Year' Seen in 1992
Abitibi-Price said it had a fourth-quarter loss of 48.1
million Canadian dollars (US$40.6 million), or 70 Canadian
cents a share, compared with a loss of C$34.7 million, or 51
Canadian cents a share, a year earlier. The latest quarter
included restructuring charges of C$24.4 million, compared
with charges of C$11.5 million in the year-earlier period.
   The Toronto pulp and paper concern said revenue fell 12%
to C$652.1 million in the fourth quarter from C$743.3 million
in the year-earlier period.